  "text": "where Φ stands for either H u or H d , and ψ is a standard model fermion. The dimension 6 operators O 6 Φ,i may produce a Z boson (longitudinal or otherwise) instead of or in addition to any higgs boson production. The dimension 6 operator O 6 ψ will produce a difermion pair instead. [CITATION_1] The effects of O 6 ψ , but not the others, were considered in Ref. [9] . We have omitted two possible R-symmetric operators, ∂ µ ζσ ν λ † F µν and ∂ µ ζσ ν λ † F µν , which could mediate the decay of the bino to a photon or Z and the goldstino. It is clear by examining the original lagrangian of Eq. (3.7) that in the R-symmetric limit with M 1 = 0, a decay to a photon cannot occur at tree-level, so that any effects of such operators will be suppressed compared to the others of the same mass dimension.",
